Brazilian Stock Movers: Celesc, Cosan Advance; Ambev Declines

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-04-04T20:57:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-cosan-advance-ambev-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index gained 0.6 percent to 69,703.80.  Cia. de Bebidas das Americas (AMBV4 BS) fell 1.5 percent to
46.10 reais. SABMiller Plc may bid for local rival Primo
Schincariol Industria de Cervejas e Refrigerantes, the Sunday
Times of  London  said, without saying where it got the
information. Heineken NV is also interested in privately owned
Schincariol, according to the newspaper.  Cosan SA Industria e Comercio (CSAN3)  (CSAN3 BS) gained 1.4 percent
to 26.45 reais. The company, which shares control of the worldâ€™s
biggest sugar-cane processor, followed higher sugar prices.
Refined-sugar futures for May delivery rose as much as 2 percent
on NYSE Liffe.  Centrais Eletricas de Santa Catarina SA (CLSC6)  (CLSC6 BS) gained
0.8 percent to 43.65 reais. Celesc, as the utility controlled by
the Brazilian state of Santa Catarina is known, may spin off its
electricity generation assets and sell a stake to private
investors, newspaper  Valor Economico  reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Antonio Gavazzoni.  To contact the reporter on this story:
